<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../../../modules/helptools/help.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>fr</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>expm  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>$LastChangedDate$</DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="expm"> exponentielle de matrice  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>expm(X)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>X  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : matrice carrée réelle ou complexe
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
    Pour <VERB>X</VERB> une matrice carrée <VERB>expm(X)</VERB> est la matrice
  </P>
  <P>
    expm(X) = I + X + X^2 /2 + ...
  </P>
  <P>
    Le calcul fait appel à une 
    bloc-diagonalisation préliminaire de <VERB>X</VERB> suivie d&apos;une approximation 
    de Padé sur chaque bloc.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
X=[1 2;3 4]
expm(X)
logm(expm(X))    
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
  <SEE_ALSO>
    <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>logm</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>bdiag</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>coff</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>log</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>exp</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>
  </SEE_ALSO>
</MAN>
